Philip Shaibu, the Edo State Deputy Governor, says the era of godfatherism is over in Nigeria, adding that it is now time for good leadership and progressives leadership to be enthroned in the country.
Shaibu who disclosed this on Saturday while speaking at the installation of the Minister of State for Budget and National Planning, Clem Agba, as the Odumha of Auchi at the Otaru of Auchi Palace, said it is high time men that have intellect like Vice President Yemi Osinbajo be voted to lead the country.
Shaibu described Prof. Yemi Osinbajo as the best candidate for the position.
READ ALSO: Obaseki ripping off LGs fund in Edo, NULGE cries out
Vice President who was the Special Guest of Honour at the occasion is yet to decide on joining the 2023 presidential race amid calls by Nigerians urging him to rescue the nation
The Deputy Governor insisted that the era of Godfatherism was over in the country, pledging his total support for Prof. Yemi Osinbajo.
He said, “Your Excellency, just know that you have all of us in Edo, you have us, anything that you want to do, you have us and you have God. And by the Grace of God, we will have our own as the President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria come 2023.
“By the special grace of God, we will mobilise ourselves so that we can take our destiny in our hands. The EndSARS was a clarion call to all of us not just in Edo but the entire nation.
“The era of godfathers is over in this country, it is now the era of good leadership and progressive leadership. Men that have intellect, men that will turn our state into an industrial state so that those who are unemployed will be gainfully employed.
